				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Death of the DoT soloing Bard<a name="1590"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 02 10:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What your friend was referrig to was the new stacking of DOT's.
<br />

<br />
Say you have 3 shaman all level 49. They can all cast Envenomed bolt DOT on the same mob and they will stack. So instead of 1100 Dmg from 1 shaman you now have 3300 dmg from 3 shaman. 
<br />

<br />
When they announce this change , we thought it woulc be great for bards as they could get 6 bards all casting Chants on the same mob. But VI did not allow stacking of our DOT's like they did for other classes. The reason being is that our DOT's also are debuffs. So if each person landed a Chant of flame and lowered the Mobs FR by 30 , then 6 bards could theoretically lower it by 180 points. VI did not want this. So they made any DOT songs that Debuff, unstackable. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
But we can still stack different songs together like before. Essentially this stacking code change was of no effect to Bards.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Torfo Tunetwister
Virtuoso- Luclin Server-
Member of Heroes
